msgid "Autoloads versus regular nodes"
msgstr "Autoloads i gcoinne nóid rialta"

msgid ""
"Godot offers a feature to automatically load nodes at the root of your "
"project, allowing you to access them globally, that can fulfill the role of "
"a Singleton: :ref:`doc_singletons_autoload`. These autoloaded nodes are not "
"freed when you change the scene from code with :ref:`SceneTree."
"change_scene_to_file <class_SceneTree_method_change_scene_to_file>`."
msgstr ""
"Cuireann Godot gné ar fáil chun nóid a luchtú go huathoibríoch ag bun an "
"tionscadail, rud a ligeann duit rochtain a fháil orthu go domhanda, ar "
"féidir leo ról Singleton a chomhlíonadh: :ref:`doc_singletons_autoload`. Ní "
"scaoiltear na nóid uathlódála seo nuair a athraíonn tú an radharc ón gcód "
"le :ref:`SceneTree.change_scene_to_file "
"<class_SceneTree_method_change_scene_to_file>`."

msgid ""
"In this guide, you will learn when to use the Autoload feature, and "
"techniques you can use to avoid it."
msgstr ""
"Sa treoir seo, foghlaimeoidh tú cathain is féidir an ghné Autoload a úsáid, "
"agus teicnící is féidir leat a úsáid chun í a sheachaint."

msgid "The cutting audio issue"
msgstr "An saincheist fuaime gearrtha"

msgid ""
"Other engines can encourage the use of creating manager classes, singletons "
"that organize a lot of functionality into a globally accessible object. "
"Godot offers many ways to avoid global state thanks to the node tree and "
"signals."
msgstr ""
"Is féidir le hinnill eile úsáid a bhaint as ranganna bainisteoirí a chruthú, "
"singiltons a eagraítear go leor feidhmiúlacht ina réad atá inrochtana ar fud "
"an domhain a spreagadh. Tugann Godot go leor bealaí chun staid dhomhanda a "
"sheachaint a bhuíochas leis an gcrann nód agus na comharthaí."

msgid ""
"For example, let's say we are building a platformer and want to collect "
"coins that play a sound effect. There's a node for that: the :ref:"
"`AudioStreamPlayer <class_AudioStreamPlayer>`. But if we call the "
"``AudioStreamPlayer`` while it is already playing a sound, the new sound "
"interrupts the first."
msgstr ""
"Mar shampla, a ligean ar a rá go bhfuil muid ag tógáil platformer agus ba "
"mhaith liom a bhailiú boinn a imríonn éifeacht fuaime. Tá nód chuige sin: "
"an :ref:`AudioStreamPlayer <class_AudioStreamPlayer>`. Ach má thugaimid an "
"``AudioStreamPlayer`` agus é ag seinm fuaime cheana féin, cuireann an fhuaim "
"nua isteach ar an gcéad cheann."

msgid ""
"A solution is to code a global, autoloaded sound manager class. It generates "
"a pool of ``AudioStreamPlayer`` nodes that cycle through as each new request "
"for sound effects comes in. Say we call that class ``Sound``, you can use it "
"from anywhere in your project by calling ``Sound.play(\"coin_pickup."
"ogg\")``. This solves the problem in the short term but causes more problems:"
msgstr ""
"Is é an réiteach ná rang bainisteora fuaime domhanda, uathoibrithe a chódú. "
"Gineann sé linn de nóid ``AudioStreamPlayer` a thioclaíonn tríd de réir mar "
"a thagann gach iarratas nua ar éifeachtaí fuaime isteach. Abair go nglaoimid "
"an rang sin ``Sound``, is féidir leat é a úsáid ó áit ar bith i do "
"thionscadal trí ghlaoch ar ``Sound.play (” coin_pickup.ogg “) ``. Réitíonn "
"sé seo an fhadhb sa ghearrthéarma ach is cúis le níos mó fadhbanna:"

msgid ""
"**Global state**: one object is now responsible for all objects' data. If "
"the ``Sound`` class has errors or doesn't have an AudioStreamPlayer "
"available, all the nodes calling it can break."
msgstr ""
"**Stát domhana**: tá réad amháin freagrach anois as sonraí gach réad. Má tá "
"earráidí ag an rang ``Fuaim` nó mura bhfuil AudioStreamPlayer ar fáil aige, "
"is féidir leis na nóid go léir a ghlaonn air briseadh."

msgid ""
"**Global access**: now that any object can call ``Sound.play(sound_path)`` "
"from anywhere, there's no longer an easy way to find the source of a bug."
msgstr ""
"**Rochtain domhana**: anois gur féidir le haon rud a ghlaoch ar `Sound.play "
"(sound_path) ``ó áit ar bith, níl bealach éasca ann a thuilleadh chun foinse "
"fabht a aimsiú."

msgid ""
"**Global resource allocation**: with a pool of ``AudioStreamPlayer`` nodes "
"stored from the start, you can either have too few and face bugs, or too "
"many and use more memory than you need."
msgstr ""
"** Leithdháileadh acmhainní domhana**: le linn nóid ``AudioStreamPlayer` "
"stóráilte ón tús, is féidir leat an róbheagán agus fabhtanna a aghaidh a "
"thabhairt duit, nó an iomarca agus níos mó cuimhne a úsáid ná mar a "
"theastaíonn uait."

msgid ""
"About global access, the problem is that any code anywhere could pass wrong "
"data to the ``Sound`` autoload in our example. As a result, the domain to "
"explore to fix the bug spans the entire project."
msgstr ""
"Maidir le rochtain dhomhanda, is í an fhadhb ná go bhféadfadh aon chód áit "
"ar bith sonraí míchearta a chur chuig an “Fuaim” uathoibríoch inár sampla. "
"Mar thoradh air sin, cuimsíonn an fearann atá le iniúchadh chun an fabht a "
"shocrú ar an tionscadal iomlán."

msgid ""
"When you keep code inside a scene, only one or two scripts may be involved "
"in audio."
msgstr ""
"Nuair a choinníonn tú cód taobh istigh de radharc, ní fhéadfaidh ach script "
"amháin nó dhó a bheith bainteach le fuaim."

msgid ""
"Contrast this with each scene keeping as many ``AudioStreamPlayer`` nodes as "
"it needs within itself and all these problems go away:"
msgstr ""
"Déan é seo i gcodarsnacht le gach radharc ag coinneáil an oiread nóid "
"``AudioStreamplayer`` agus is gá dó féin agus imíonn na fadhbanna seo go "
"léir as:"

msgid ""
"Each scene manages its own state information. If there is a problem with the "
"data, it will only cause issues in that one scene."
msgstr ""
"Bainistíonn gach radharc a fhaisnéis stáit féin. Má tá fadhb leis na sonraí, "
"ní chruthóidh sé ach saincheisteanna sa radharc amháin sin."

msgid ""
"Each scene accesses only its own nodes. Now, if there is a bug, it's easy to "
"find which node is at fault."
msgstr ""
"Ní bhíonn rochtain ag gach radharc ach ar a nóid féin. Anois, má tá fabht "
"ann, is furasta a aimsiú cén nód atá ar locht."

msgid "Each scene allocates exactly the amount of resources it needs."
msgstr "Leithdháileann gach radharc go díreach an méid acmhainní atá uaidh."

msgid "Managing shared functionality or data"
msgstr "Feidhmiúlacht nó sonraí comhroinnte"

msgid ""
"Another reason to use an Autoload can be that you want to reuse the same "
"method or data across many scenes."
msgstr ""
"Is féidir cúis eile le Autoload a úsáid ná gur mhaith leat an modh nó na "
"sonraí céanna a athúsáid thar go leor radhairc."

msgid ""
"In the case of functions, you can create a new type of ``Node`` that "
"provides that feature for an individual scene using the :ref:`class_name "
"<doc_gdscript_basics_class_name>` keyword in GDScript."
msgstr ""
"I gcás feidhmeanna, is féidir leat cineál nua ``Nóid`` a chruthú a "
"sholáthraíonn an ghné sin do radharc aonair ag baint úsáide as an :ref:"
"`class_name <doc_gdscript_basics_class_name>` eochairfhocal i GDScript."

msgid "When it comes to data, you can either:"
msgstr "Maidir le sonraí, is féidir leat:"

msgid ""
"Create a new type of :ref:`Resource <class_Resource>` to share the data."
msgstr ""
"Cruthaigh cineál nua :ref:`Acmhainn <class_Resource>` chun na sonraí a "
"roinnt."

msgid ""
"Store the data in an object to which each node has access, for example using "
"the ``owner`` property to access the scene's root node."
msgstr ""
"Stóráil na sonraí i réad a bhfuil rochtain ag gach nód air, mar shampla ag "
"baint úsáide as an maoin ``úinéir ``chun rochtain a fháil ar fhréamhnód an "
"radhairc."

msgid "When you should use an Autoload"
msgstr "Cathain ba chóir duit Autoload a úsáid"

msgid ""
"GDScript supports the creation of ``static`` functions using ``static "
"func``. When combined with ``class_name``, this makes it possible to create "
"libraries of helper functions without having to create an instance to call "
"them. The limitation of static functions is that they can't reference member "
"variables, non-static functions or ``self``."
msgstr ""
"Tacaíonn GDScript le cruthú feidhmeanna `static`` ag baint úsáide as "
"``function statach``. Nuair a dhéantar é a chomhcheangal le `class_name``, "
"is féidir leabharlanna feidhmeanna cúntóra a chruthú gan sampla a chruthú "
"chun glaoch orthu. Is é an teorannú ar fheidhmeanna statacha nach féidir leo "
"tagairt a dhéanamh ar athróga ball, feidhmeanna neamh-statacha nó ``féin`."

msgid ""
"Still, autoloaded nodes can simplify your code for systems with a wide "
"scope. If the autoload is managing its own information and not invading the "
"data of other objects, then it's a great way to create systems that handle "
"broad-scoped tasks. For example, a quest or a dialogue system."
msgstr ""
"Fós féin, is féidir le nóid uathoibríoch do chód a shimpliú do chórais a "
"bhfuil raon feidhme leathan acu. Má tá an t-autoload ag bainistiú a "
"fhaisnéis féin agus gan ionradh ar shonraí rudaí eile, ansin is bealach "
"iontach é chun córais a chruthú a láimhseálann tascanna scóip leathan. Mar "
"shampla, cuardach nó córas idirphlé."

msgid ""
"An autoload is *not* necessarily a singleton. Nothing prevents you from "
"instantiating copies of an autoloaded node. An autoload is only a tool that "
"makes a node load automatically as a child of the root of your scene tree, "
"regardless of your game's node structure or which scene you run, e.g. by "
"pressing the :kbd:`F6` key."
msgstr ""
"Ní gá gur singleton é uathlódáil. Ní chuireann aon rud cosc ort cóipeanna de "
"nód uathlódáilte a chur ar an toirt. Níl in uath-ualach ach uirlis a "
"dhéanann ualach nód go huathoibríoch mar leanbh de fhréamh do chrann "
"radhairc, beag beann ar struchtúr nód do chluiche nó cén radharc a ritheann "
"tú, e.g. trí an eochair :kbd:`F6` a bhrú."

msgid ""
"As a result, you can get the autoloaded node, for example an autoload called "
"``Sound``, by calling ``get_node(\"/root/Sound\")``."
msgstr ""
"Mar thoradh air sin, is féidir leat an nód autoloaded a fháil, mar shampla "
"uathoibríoch ar a dtugtar ``Sound``, trí ghlaoch ar ``get_node (“/root/"
"sound”) ``."
